                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">Tutor Policy</span><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">(Updated on August, 2023)</span></p>
                    <p><br></p>
                    <hr>
                    <p><br></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">If you want to offer Tutor Services on the Speakede Platform, you must read and agree to be bound by these policies for Tutors (&quot;Tutor Policy&quot;). Capitalized terms (including the term &quot;Speakede&quot;) used but not defined in this Tutor Policy have the meanings ascribed to such terms in our Terms of Service, which is available at&nbsp;</span><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/u/0/d/1U10mGJaO7_zHE64OCaGLQK1ZXA2kCUMvlWvbCpHpiww/edit"><u><span style="color:#1155cc;font-size:10.5pt;">here&nbsp;</span></u></a><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">(the &quot;Speakede Terms&quot;).</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">If you do not accept this Tutor Policy in full, you are not authorized to tutor on the Speakede Platform and you are not eligible to receive any benefits from Speakede for any Tutor Services you provide.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">This Tutor Policy is designed to encourage the highest standards of Tutor behavior in their relationships with Learners by setting clear expectations, and to provide the principles to guide Tutors in their daily conduct when providing Tutor Services and interacting with Learners. However, our Tutors come from all over the world and are thus accustomed to a variety of different cultural norms. As a result, this Tutor Policy attempts to adopt universally accepted standards of respect and tolerance. This Tutor Policy does not attempt to address every potential situation that could arise when Tutors interact with Learners on the Speakede Platform, but instead provides principles for ethical and professional behavior that can serve as guidance regarding Speakede expectations.</span></p>
                    <p><br></p>
                    <hr>
                    <p><br></p>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">1. Tutor Registration and Service Description</span></strong></h5>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">1.1 Tutor Signup</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">In order to become a &quot;Tutor&quot;, you must first Signup and create a lesson on the Speakede Platform and you can begin providing &quot;Tutor Services&quot;, including offering and providing paid lessons (&quot;Lesson&quot;) to Learners.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">To the extent permitted by applicable law, Speakede may obtain (i) background check reports from public records or through third party vendors regarding matters such as criminal convictions or sex offender registrations, and/or (ii) identity verification check reports. As a condition of engaging the Speakede Platform as a Tutor, you agree and authorize us to use your personal information, such as your full name and date of birth, to obtain such reports..</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">1.2 Tutor Services Description</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">All Tutors must create a description of their Tutor Services on the Speakede Platform. When creating the description of your tutoring Services, you agree to the following:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Write a specific, detailed service description with clear tutoring scope and Lessons;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Set expectations that you can meet or exceed;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Do not offer services with the intent to commit fraud, provide services other than those outlined in your description, or offer any services in exchange for positive feedback or at no cost;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Do not advertise any third-party tutoring service, platform, software, or application; and</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Do not include any personal contact information, including but not limited to, email, telephone number, or social media account number.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">2. Tutor Services Guidelines</span></strong></h5>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">2.1 Tutor Service Request</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Once you receive a Tutor Service request from a Learner, you agree to the following:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Use the Speakede Platform to manage all Tutor Service requests from Learners;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Respond promptly to all Tutor Services related communications, whether from a Learner or from Speakede;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Maintain a record of all important details of the communication between you and the Learner. For the avoidance of doubt, communication may be conducted via emails, instant messages, telephone or in-person conversations, and important details generally includes information related to the scope of your Tutor Services, your time frames and availability to provide any Tutor Service, your price, your feedback to Learner, any schedule changes, any delay of providing your Tutor Service, and completion of Lessons; and</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Respond to all Tutor Services requests with accept, decline, or propose a time/date change. Do not ignore tutoring Service requests and allow them to expire.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">2.2 Lesson Policy</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">All Tutors are expected to comply with the following policies when providing a Lesson:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Commit to your scheduled Lesson. A confirmed Lesson is a commitment you make with a Learner. Reschedule or cancel as a last resort and only after you have communicated this with your Learner. If you know you will be away and unable to respond to Learners for a certain period, take the responsibility to notify your Learners of your absence and update the availability information on your Speakede Account profile accordingly.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Make records. Tutors should maintain a record of all important details of communications with the Learners pursuant to Section 2.1(3). If there is a dispute between Tutor and Learner, Speakede will request both Tutor and Learner to provide evidence in the format of screenshots, and such screenshots shall contain all information related to such dispute, such as the date, time and other communication details.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Start Tutor Services on time. Tutors should start any Lesson at the time scheduled with the Learner, and should initiate contact with the Learner, particularly with a first-time Learner.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Connect with the Learner. Tutors should connect with their Learners on the agreed communication platform well before the scheduled start time for the Lesson. Don&rsquo;t wait until the last minute.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Waiting for a late Learner. If a Learner is late for a scheduled Lesson, the Tutor should wait for the Learner until the end of the period for the scheduled Lesson. The Tutor should be available to start the Lesson at any time during the scheduled period for the Lesson. The Tutor is not, however, required to make up for lost time due to the Learner&apos;s late arrival.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">End Lesson on time. Tutors should politely let Learners know that their lessons are ending by reminding them before the end of the Lesson time period. You may politely tell the Learner that you need to prepare for an upcoming Lesson with another Learner.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Rescheduling a Lesson due to Learner&rsquo;s absence. If a Learner fails to attend a Lesson and requests to reschedule the class, it is the Tutor decision to agree or reject.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Additional Information is available at&nbsp;</span><a href="https://support.italki.com/hc/en-us/articles/360020529954-Lesson-Policy"><u><span style="color:#59789b;font-size:10.5pt;">Lesson Policy</span></u></a><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">2.3 Cancellation and Rescheduling</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">If you will be unable to provide your Tutor Services at the time previously agreed between you and a Learner, you agree to (i) immediately inform the Learner that you are unable to provide your Tutor Services at the scheduled time, and provide the Learner with an explanation; and (ii) immediately inform Speakede Support. If you were unable to inform the Learner in advance due to an emergency, you are required to give an explanation to the Learner as soon as you are able to do so.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">After obtaining the consent from the Learner, a Tutor may cancel or reschedule any scheduled Tutor Service (including a Lesson) at any time that is more than 24 hours before such Tutor Service is scheduled to start. Canceling or rescheduling a Tutor Service must be handled through the Speakede Platform, and by following the&nbsp;</span><a href="https://support.speakede.com"><u><span style="color:#1155cc;font-size:10.5pt;">cancellation and rescheduling process</span></u></a><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">.</span></p>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Except in the rare case of true emergencies, no Tutor Service (including a Lesson) may be canceled or rescheduled by a Tutor or Learner within 24 hours of the start time for such Tutor Service.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">2.4 Payment and Feedback</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">After you provide any Tutor Services, you agree to the following:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Use the Speakede Payment Service to handle all financial matters related to your Tutor Services; and</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Provide helpful, objective, balanced feedback for the Learner.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">2.5 Additional Guidelines</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">You also agree the following additional guidelines in connection with providing your Tutor Services on the Speakede Platform:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Maintain the privacy of Speakede Learners pursuant to the Speakede Privacy Policy, including refraining from requesting any personally identifiable information from Learners, such as birth date, age, government issued identification number, phone number, or home address;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Maintain the privacy of your own personal information, including details related to your Tutor Wallet (as defined in the Speakede Payment Policy);</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Maintain records of all invoices and payments in connection with your Tutor Services;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Cooperate with Speakede in any anti-fraud actions and in resolving any disputes; and</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Report any violation of the Speakede Terms or any other Speakede Policies, including misuse of ratings and feedback.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">3. Service Standards</span></strong></h5>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">3.1 Be Culturally Sensitive</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Respect the values and traditions of your Learners. Unless specifically requested by the Learner, please avoid asking about the following:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Your Learner&rsquo;s personal life. For example, do not ask a Learner whether he or she is married, or whether he or she has a girlfriend or boyfriend.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Your Learner&rsquo;s political affiliations. For example, do not ask a Learner whether he or she supports a particular political party or ideological view.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Your Learner&rsquo;s religious affiliations. For example, do not ask a Learner if he or she believes in God or identifies with a particular religious group.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">3.2 Be Patient and Polite</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Since Learners come from different backgrounds and have different language abilities, it is important to be patient and polite. Help them through their language learning difficulties. Be encouraging, not discouraging.</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Do not berate, yell at, or insult a Learner. Do not tell a Learner he or she is dumb or insult their current level of language ability.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Do not use rude or offensive language with a Learner. Instead, use respectful language and speak to Learners with professional courtesy.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Do not lose your temper with a Learner.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">If you are not sure whether you are able to handle a situation with composure, you are welcome to contact Speakede Support for help, or to suggest that a Learner contact Speakede Support to resolve an issue.</span></p>
                    <h6 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:12pt;">3.3 Be Professional</span></strong></h6>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Tutors must take the initiative in communicating with and managing Learners. In addition to the Tutor Services guidelines described in Section 2 (Tutor Services Guidelines), Tutors are expected to provide Tutor Services in a professional manner, which includes:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Being responsive. You should respond to messages from Learners promptly. When you receive a Tutor Service request from a Learner, you should respond within 48 hours OR before the start time proposed by the Learner for the Tutor Service (whichever is sooner). The Speakede Platform will send you notifications when a Learner send you a message or a Tutor Service request, but we recommend that you login to your Speakede Account at least twice a day to check and respond to messages and Tutor Service requests.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Actively manage your calendar and profile. Maintain your calendar to accurately reflect the times you are available to provide Tutor Services. When you login to your Speakede Account, you should check and adjust your time availability schedule, and update your status. Learners can view a Tutor&rsquo;s last login time, so Tutors who actively manage their profile will naturally attract more Learners. If you plan to take time off from providing Tutor Services, update your profile accordingly so that you will be removed from active Tutor listings (please see:&nbsp;</span><a href="https://support.italki.com"><u><span style="color:#1155cc;font-size:10.5pt;">I need to take a break from tutoring on Speakede. What do I do?</span></u></a><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">).</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Respect Learner privacy. Recording audio or video of a Learner is not permitted without the Learner&rsquo;s prior written or recorded consent.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Teach your language. Learners are paying you to tutor them a new language. Do not use this time to practice the Learner&rsquo;s native language. Instead, give Learners more speaking time.</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Provide accurate and respectful feedback. Speakede provides a feedback and rating system to allow Learners to publicly express their opinions to their Tutor&rsquo;s instruction quality. Speakede does not monitor, censor, or investigate feedback and rating posts unless a problem is brought to our attention. If you believe a particular Learner&rsquo;s feedback or rating is improper, untrue or violates Speakede Terms or Speakede Policies, please report the incident to Speakede Support.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">4. Violation of this Tutor Policy</span></strong></h5>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">You are expected to perform any Tutor Service in a manner that satisfies the tutoring standards described above and results in a consistently high level of Learner satisfaction. You are in breach of this Tutor Policy, if you:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Fail to deliver any Tutor Service for which payment was accepted;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Fail to take reasonable efforts to resolve a dispute with a Learner;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Create unacceptable levels of Learner dissatisfaction; or</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Violate any Speakede Terms or any other Speakede Policies.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Speakede reserves the right to take any of the following actions at any time and in its sole discretion:</span></p>
                    <ol>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Cancel your listed Tutor Services;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Limit your Speakede Account privileges;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Adjust your Tutor Wallet balance and/or freeze or suspend your Tutor Wallet;</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Suspend or terminate your Speakede Account; or</span></p>
                        </li>
                        <li style="list-style-type:decimal;color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">
                            <p style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#515164;font-size:10.5pt;">Contact law enforcement or seek legal remedies.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <h5 style="color:#ffffff;background-color:#ffffff;"><strong><span style="color:#313140;font-size:15pt;">5. Tutor Content</span></strong></h5>
